2
00:00:04,124 --> 00:00:09,580
(VIEWER DISCRETION IS ADVISED.)

3
00:00:11,874 --> 00:00:14,174
Yes. That's why I'm saying this.

4
00:00:14,174 --> 00:00:15,714
(EPISODE 16)

5
00:00:15,714 --> 00:00:19,044
I'm saying this because today is just about right.

6
00:00:22,374 --> 00:00:25,214
I'm saying this because you are still shining.

7
00:00:27,814 --> 00:00:32,144
I'm saying this because you were that first love.

8
00:00:33,474 --> 00:00:35,584
On another day that is just about right,

9
00:00:36,314 --> 00:00:38,744
will you be my bride?

10
00:01:15,614 --> 00:01:16,914
I will.

11
00:01:18,114 --> 00:01:21,214
I will be the bride of this lonely man.

12
00:01:23,014 --> 00:01:24,844
I will be...

13
00:01:26,144 --> 00:01:29,174
the first and the last bride of this beautiful man.

14
00:01:29,674 --> 00:01:31,344
I most definitely will be.

15
00:02:10,044 --> 00:02:11,114
Mom.

16
00:02:11,774 --> 00:02:13,344
I'm getting married.

17
00:02:14,914 --> 00:02:16,414
I'll be happy.

18
00:02:22,114 --> 00:02:24,774
I see you met the goblin.

19
00:02:25,344 --> 00:02:27,514
And you're getting married.

20
00:02:27,514 --> 00:02:28,774
Good for you.

21
00:02:30,074 --> 00:02:31,914
Why am I tearing up?

22
00:02:33,714 --> 00:02:34,774
Hey!

23
00:02:38,184 --> 00:02:40,244
- Do you see us?
- Yes.

24
00:02:40,344 --> 00:02:42,974
How long has it been? How have you been?

25
00:02:42,974 --> 00:02:46,114
You finally see us again.

26
00:02:46,114 --> 00:02:47,514
You startled me.

27
00:02:48,414 --> 00:02:50,244
Have you been doing okay?

28
00:02:50,914 --> 00:02:52,274
We were lonely, that's all.

29
00:02:53,814 --> 00:02:55,274
Come with me.

30
00:02:56,174 --> 00:02:57,874
I'll treat you better than the goblin does.

31
00:02:59,474 --> 00:03:02,744
Wait here. I have a sack of salt somewhere to...

32
00:03:02,744 --> 00:03:06,044
You still have the same fiery temper.

33
00:03:07,714 --> 00:03:08,814
Congratulations.

34
00:03:09,574 --> 00:03:11,774
- You're getting married.
- Congratulations.

35
00:03:18,814 --> 00:03:19,944
Drink it.

36
00:03:20,344 --> 00:03:22,914
It'll remove your memories from your life.

37
00:03:23,044 --> 00:03:24,474
Thank you.

38
00:03:24,474 --> 00:03:26,944
What kind of nonsense is this?

39
00:03:26,944 --> 00:03:29,114
I won't share a table with my driver.

40
00:03:29,114 --> 00:03:30,514
Or drink the same tea.

41
00:03:30,514 --> 00:03:33,674
Here, everyone gets the same cup of tea.

42
00:03:33,674 --> 00:03:36,244
What logic is that? I'm upset as it is to be dead.

43
00:03:36,244 --> 00:03:38,744
Why should I be treated the same as...

44
00:03:38,744 --> 00:03:42,014
the likes of a man whose whole life isn't worth the watch on my wrist?

45
00:03:42,174 --> 00:03:43,874
I will tell you again.

46
00:03:44,274 --> 00:03:46,614
Here, everyone gets the same cup of tea.

47
00:03:47,414 --> 00:03:50,044
Your watch has already stopped ticking.

48
00:03:50,344 --> 00:03:52,544
Nothing you have with you...

49
00:03:53,774 --> 00:03:55,744
can pass that threshold.

50
00:03:57,874 --> 00:04:00,274
Were you a powerful man in this life?

51
00:04:00,274 --> 00:04:03,144
As soon as you go through that door, you'll realize that...

52
00:04:03,614 --> 00:04:06,974
the crimes you committed with your eyes, your mouth,

53
00:04:07,144 --> 00:04:08,944
your hands and feet...

54
00:04:08,944 --> 00:04:12,874
and heart are much more powerful than anything you knew.

55
00:04:13,944 --> 00:04:18,114
See how deep in Hades they drag you down.

56
00:04:36,344 --> 00:04:39,174
Don't you want to go on a blind date?

57
00:04:39,174 --> 00:04:40,644
I don't like chefs.

58
00:04:40,644 --> 00:04:42,314
He isn't a chef.

59
00:04:42,314 --> 00:04:44,414
He's a client of mine.

60
00:04:44,614 --> 00:04:46,614
He's rich, owns a company,

61
00:04:46,614 --> 00:04:49,544
is handsome and the crucial part is that...

62
00:04:50,174 --> 00:04:51,214
he's young.

63
00:04:52,414 --> 00:04:54,074
He likes older women.

64
00:04:54,274 --> 00:04:57,114
I consult him about inheritance issues,

65
00:04:57,114 --> 00:04:59,484
not anything shady. What do you think?

66
00:05:02,173 --> 00:05:03,703
A blind date?

67
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:17,774
Oh no. These are new.

68
00:05:18,074 --> 00:05:19,444
What just happened?

69
00:05:20,036 --> 00:05:21,976
I shouldn't be waiting here.

70
00:05:22,776 --> 00:05:24,076
Ji Eun Tak!

71
00:05:26,836 --> 00:05:29,406
What should we listen to? A new singer's song?

72
00:05:29,576 --> 00:05:30,576
Sure.

73
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,106
How can I help you?

74
00:05:36,106 --> 00:05:38,276
I'm Producer Ji's boyfriend.

75
00:05:38,936 --> 00:05:41,476
- What?
- Her fiance, to be exact.

76
00:05:41,476 --> 00:05:43,176
Shall we get hitched this weekend?

77
00:05:43,876 --> 00:05:45,106
- What?
- What?

78
00:05:45,106 --> 00:05:48,276
Shall we get some lunch first? Let's get out of here.

79
00:05:51,036 --> 00:05:52,306
Is someone joining us?

80
00:05:54,276 --> 00:05:56,576
Deok Hwa. You should say hi.

81
00:05:56,576 --> 00:05:57,976
I guess.

82
00:05:58,176 --> 00:06:01,136
What if he doesn't recognize me because I look so old?

83
00:06:01,306 --> 00:06:02,736
That will never happen.

84
00:06:02,736 --> 00:06:04,876
Can I have some soup, please?

85
00:06:04,876 --> 00:06:06,036
- Sure.
- He's here.

86
00:06:15,536 --> 00:06:18,006
An official-looking feast in front of...

87
00:06:18,006 --> 00:06:19,636
a couple sitting side-by-side.

88
00:06:21,076 --> 00:06:22,976
- I got what's going on.
- Yes.

89
00:06:23,306 --> 00:06:25,006
We're engaged.

90
00:06:25,936 --> 00:06:27,136
- What?
- What?

91
00:06:27,776 --> 00:06:29,206
Saturday or Sunday?

92
00:06:29,206 --> 00:06:31,206
What got into you today?

93
00:06:31,206 --> 00:06:33,036
Lunchtime or dinnertime?

94
00:06:33,036 --> 00:06:35,606
I prefer Sunday evening. Saturday's my night out.

95
00:06:36,806 --> 00:06:38,176
What's this about?

96
00:06:38,176 --> 00:06:41,076
Can't you tell? It's to stop you from going on blind dates.

97
00:06:41,076 --> 00:06:42,736
With a handsome rich guy...

98
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:44,576
who is younger than you.

99
00:06:44,576 --> 00:06:46,306
What are you talking about?

100
00:06:46,306 --> 00:06:49,036
I'm the only one in Korea who fits that description.

101
00:06:49,936 --> 00:06:52,206
Don't worry. You aren't my type.

102
00:06:52,936 --> 00:06:56,276
Nice to meet you. I am Yu Deok Hwa.

103
00:06:56,276 --> 00:06:58,436
Hello, I heard a lot about you.

104
00:06:58,436 --> 00:07:00,276
I am Ji Eun Tak.

105
00:07:00,606 --> 00:07:02,836
He got promoted to manager.

106
00:07:02,836 --> 00:07:04,306
Ji Eun Tak?

107
00:07:04,476 --> 00:07:06,206
The Ji Eun Tak of that old letter?

108
00:07:06,206 --> 00:07:08,136
The Ji Eun Tak who knows my tenant?

109
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:10,736
There's still a lot you don't know.

110
00:07:11,606 --> 00:07:14,106
- Enjoy your soup.
- Thanks, I will.

111
00:07:18,406 --> 00:07:19,436
So,

112
00:07:20,076 --> 00:07:21,906
do you know what my uncle is?

113
00:07:21,906 --> 00:07:25,206
He's a goblin. Doesn't everyone know one of those?

114
00:07:25,206 --> 00:07:27,106
- Correct.
- No way.

115
00:07:27,776 --> 00:07:30,276
You know about my building and my uncle.

116
00:07:30,476 --> 00:07:33,306
What's going on? Why am I the only one in the dark?

117
00:07:33,306 --> 00:07:34,406
Let's eat.

118
00:07:35,676 --> 00:07:37,106
Eat up and grow up.

119
00:07:37,106 --> 00:07:38,836
You'll find out in due time.

120
00:07:41,306 --> 00:07:42,406
Me, too.

121
00:07:47,536 --> 00:07:49,636
Don't you dare go on a blind date.

122
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,776
Why would I? I'll be a married woman soon.

123
00:07:54,906 --> 00:07:58,076
She said "married woman".

124
00:07:58,376 --> 00:07:59,736
Where do you live?

125
00:08:00,676 --> 00:08:02,776
I said you aren't my type.

126
00:08:02,776 --> 00:08:05,076
Do you like your job?

127
00:08:05,076 --> 00:08:06,736
My uncle's getting married.

128
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:08,806
That's great news.

129
00:08:08,806 --> 00:08:11,776
It is. I want to get married before he does.

130
00:08:11,776 --> 00:08:13,476
That's even greater news.

131
00:08:13,476 --> 00:08:15,606
Isn't it? I'll have lots of kids...

132
00:08:15,606 --> 00:08:17,036
so that no one's lonely.

133
00:08:17,036 --> 00:08:19,536
I could wish for nothing more.

134
00:08:19,536 --> 00:08:21,036
But Deok Hwa.

135
00:08:21,776 --> 00:08:23,706
You need a partner to get married.

136
00:08:24,106 --> 00:08:25,536
I have lots of women.

137
00:08:25,536 --> 00:08:28,936
Yes, and that's the problem. You can't have many women.

138
00:08:32,506 --> 00:08:35,806
Was there anyone who made your heart pound?

139
00:08:35,906 --> 00:08:39,046
Anyone you missed to the point of wanting to cry?

140
00:08:39,046 --> 00:08:42,676
Was there anyone who made you think you'd be willing to...

141
00:08:42,876 --> 00:08:44,806
die for that person?

142
00:08:46,436 --> 00:08:47,576
Not yet.

143
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:51,806
Don't you want to get married?

144
00:08:53,046 --> 00:08:54,636
- I don't.
- Why not?

145
00:08:54,636 --> 00:08:56,406
I'm already married with three kids.

146
00:08:56,406 --> 00:08:58,076
I married such a person.

147
00:08:58,076 --> 00:09:00,276
No way. Did you really?

148
00:09:00,476 --> 00:09:02,506
- Why didn't I know that?
- I never told you.

149
00:09:02,506 --> 00:09:05,106
- Why didn't you tell me?
- You never asked.

150
00:09:07,976 --> 00:09:09,376
You don't care much about...

151
00:09:09,376 --> 00:09:12,576
the people around you or how the world works.

152
00:09:12,676 --> 00:09:15,406
That's why I'm waiting for you to ask questions.

153
00:09:15,636 --> 00:09:17,806
Questions that an adult would ask.

154
00:09:19,106 --> 00:09:20,706
About the world...

155
00:09:21,106 --> 00:09:24,836
and about the joy and sorrows of those around you.

156
00:09:30,076 --> 00:09:31,276
Thank you.

157
00:09:32,976 --> 00:09:34,676
Give me a little more time.

158
00:09:35,136 --> 00:09:38,046
I'll try my best to grow up.

159
00:09:38,876 --> 00:09:40,176
You do that.

160
00:09:48,046 --> 00:09:50,276
How could you just come out and tell everyone...

161
00:09:50,276 --> 00:09:52,046
without my permission?

162
00:09:52,046 --> 00:09:54,136
Eyes on the road. A car's coming.

163
00:09:54,136 --> 00:09:55,406
Watch out.

164
00:09:56,136 --> 00:09:57,306
Are you afraid?

165
00:09:57,306 --> 00:09:59,836
No. Watching you drive makes me think...

166
00:09:59,836 --> 00:10:01,876
you're all grown up. Stay in your lane.

167
00:10:01,876 --> 00:10:04,306
- Keep your hands on the wheel.
- I am.

168
00:10:04,306 --> 00:10:07,436
I know you are, I just find it fascinating, that's all.

169
00:10:07,436 --> 00:10:09,106
I've never been a passenger before.

170
00:10:10,306 --> 00:10:12,776
- Turn left here.
- Left?

171
00:10:12,776 --> 00:10:15,476
Not right, left, left!

172
00:10:16,546 --> 00:10:19,906
Stop yelling. Where are we going anyway?

173
00:10:20,636 --> 00:10:23,576
Turn on the blinkers before you make a turn!

174
00:10:49,876 --> 00:10:51,706
You look so pretty.

175
00:10:54,636 --> 00:10:57,276
You look pretty nice yourself.

176
00:10:57,436 --> 00:10:59,376
I always do.

177
00:11:03,376 --> 00:11:05,976
Let's get married with a bowl of water.

178
00:11:06,136 --> 00:11:07,576
Keep it mysterious.

179
00:11:08,306 --> 00:11:09,436
Okay.

180
00:11:19,436 --> 00:11:20,806
Is it a gift?

181
00:11:21,176 --> 00:11:22,776
A wedding gift.

182
00:11:24,806 --> 00:11:27,136
He has pretty wrists.

183
00:11:27,406 --> 00:11:28,906
I'll take this one.

184
00:12:11,436 --> 00:12:13,876
I love all the roads we will walk together.

185
00:12:13,876 --> 00:12:16,306
I love all the sceneries we will see together.

186
00:12:16,376 --> 00:12:18,676
I love all the questions we will shyly ask each other...

187
00:12:18,676 --> 00:12:21,576
and all the answers to those questions.

188
00:12:21,576 --> 00:12:23,736
I love you...

189
00:12:23,776 --> 00:12:27,276
in all those moments. From your bride.

190
00:12:27,306 --> 00:12:31,106
After we listen to a song, we will come back with a listener's story.

191
00:12:31,106 --> 00:12:32,136
Cue.

192
00:12:33,436 --> 00:12:35,036
What is this letter?

193
00:12:35,176 --> 00:12:36,976
It's so poorly written.

194
00:12:37,076 --> 00:12:39,306
Was this written at night?

195
00:12:39,306 --> 00:12:41,676
What is it? I love love letters.

196
00:12:41,676 --> 00:12:43,306
I'm sure you do.

197
00:12:44,676 --> 00:12:46,206
"To the one who thought..."

198
00:12:46,236 --> 00:12:48,576
"that oblivion would bring me peace of mind."

199
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:51,136
"The moment our eyes met, I knew..."

200
00:12:51,206 --> 00:12:54,076
"that you too retained your memories."

201
00:12:54,076 --> 00:12:56,106
Pick this story. It's my right as the producer.

202
00:12:56,106 --> 00:12:57,306
I'll be back soon.

203
00:12:57,306 --> 00:12:59,276
Eun Tak! Hey!

204
00:12:59,276 --> 00:13:01,176
This is a live show!

205
00:13:01,206 --> 00:13:03,836
"I pray that in our next life..."

206
00:13:04,176 --> 00:13:08,606
"The wait will be short and the meeting shall be long."

207
00:13:09,376 --> 00:13:12,806
"That we won't need an excuse to see each other."

208
00:13:13,576 --> 00:13:17,736
"Entitled with our own dearest names."

209
00:13:20,806 --> 00:13:22,306
"So we could greet each other..."

210
00:13:22,406 --> 00:13:24,736
"when we accidentally run into each other."

211
00:13:25,676 --> 00:13:28,376
With our love always being the solution.

212
00:13:29,406 --> 00:13:31,776
I pray that we can meet like that.

213
00:13:33,106 --> 00:13:35,576
I'm just happy that I saw your face.

214
00:13:36,306 --> 00:13:38,476
Sometimes, you're Kim Woo Bin.

215
00:13:38,876 --> 00:13:42,376
And sometimes, you're Wang Yeo.

216
00:13:43,876 --> 00:13:45,206
Please live a long...

217
00:13:45,736 --> 00:13:47,236
and happy life.

218
00:13:49,976 --> 00:13:51,436
Goodbye.

219
00:13:52,576 --> 00:13:56,106
Did she really sell the building? Didn't she just move?

220
00:13:56,106 --> 00:13:59,376
No. She sold the building last week. You live on the rooftop, right?

221
00:13:59,376 --> 00:14:01,976
You're my tenant now.

222
00:14:02,006 --> 00:14:03,906
I heard you work for a radio station.

223
00:14:03,906 --> 00:14:05,836
Yes.

224
00:14:05,836 --> 00:14:08,936
I'm in a little bit of a hurry right now. I'll see you later.

225
00:14:12,376 --> 00:14:13,406
(THE ROOFTOP UNIT)

226
00:14:23,136 --> 00:14:24,306
Eun Tak.

227
00:14:24,636 --> 00:14:25,976
I'm leaving.

228
00:14:26,136 --> 00:14:28,536
Take care. Don't cry.

229
00:14:28,836 --> 00:14:31,076
Get something to eat.

230
00:14:31,376 --> 00:14:34,806
You were all alone without a family.

231
00:14:34,906 --> 00:14:37,506
I hope I provided you a little bit of comfort.

232
00:14:38,076 --> 00:14:40,576
Please take good care of my stubborn brother.

233
00:14:40,576 --> 00:14:42,836
Stay happy together.

234
00:14:43,176 --> 00:14:44,436
Goodbye.

235
00:14:48,476 --> 00:14:50,836
She remembered everything.

236
00:14:55,676 --> 00:14:56,936
Sunny...

237
00:14:59,106 --> 00:15:00,636
left.

238
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:05,406
She remembered everything.

239
00:15:05,876 --> 00:15:08,036
She kept the memory alone.

240
00:15:08,036 --> 00:15:10,436
She took care of me when I didn't remember anything.

241
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:13,006
She missed her brother who disappeared.

242
00:15:13,176 --> 00:15:15,306
She must've been so lonely.

243
00:15:18,006 --> 00:15:20,136
Why did she leave now?

244
00:15:20,206 --> 00:15:22,406
It's because she can't forgive him.

245
00:15:23,876 --> 00:15:25,406
She made the choice...

246
00:15:26,936 --> 00:15:29,106
not to see him again in this life.

247
00:15:30,876 --> 00:15:32,476
There's no bigger punishment...

248
00:15:33,276 --> 00:15:35,506
for the Grim Reaper.

249
00:15:50,676 --> 00:15:54,236
I should count to 50 and leave.

250
00:15:55,776 --> 00:15:57,036
One.

251
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:01,576
Two.

252
00:16:04,376 --> 00:16:07,176
47.

253
00:16:07,176 --> 00:16:09,776
48.

254
00:16:12,106 --> 00:16:14,806
49.

255
00:16:17,260 --> 00:16:18,360
One.

256
00:16:33,665 --> 00:16:34,765
Two.

257
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,445
Three.

258
00:16:45,276 --> 00:16:46,536
You will...

259
00:16:47,576 --> 00:16:49,706
not hear from me.

260
00:16:53,906 --> 00:16:55,676
In this life,

261
00:16:59,136 --> 00:17:01,236
we will never meet again.

262
00:17:06,176 --> 00:17:07,606
Can I...

263
00:17:08,876 --> 00:17:10,806
hug you just once?

264
00:17:46,176 --> 00:17:47,776
Take care.

265
00:17:49,936 --> 00:17:51,176
Take care.

266
00:17:58,476 --> 00:17:59,976
Like that,

267
00:18:01,176 --> 00:18:03,746
we parted in this life.

268
00:18:06,006 --> 00:18:08,406
It was...

269
00:18:09,576 --> 00:18:11,076
much later...

270
00:18:11,476 --> 00:18:13,176
when I heard from her.

271
00:18:42,276 --> 00:18:45,006
I touched this vulgar thing for you.

272
00:18:45,306 --> 00:18:46,936
Why don't you try it?

273
00:18:49,006 --> 00:18:52,006
The apples look like bunnies.

274
00:18:55,776 --> 00:18:57,406
