had its brake come loose and rolled down,

553
00:39:25,098 --> 00:39:27,598
taking the life of a woman in her 20s.

554
00:39:27,598 --> 00:39:30,258
That car must have taken all the shock.

555
00:39:30,788 --> 00:39:32,228
My goodness.

556
00:39:32,958 --> 00:39:34,758
She must've been an angel.

557
00:39:34,758 --> 00:39:37,788
I believe that she's not an ordinary person.

558
00:39:38,628 --> 00:39:40,628
Had it not been for her,

559
00:39:40,758 --> 00:39:43,258
a lot more people would have died.

560
00:39:45,458 --> 00:39:47,958
Is this the place...

561
00:39:47,988 --> 00:39:49,728
you work at?

562
00:39:50,428 --> 00:39:51,928
It's really nice.

563
00:39:53,488 --> 00:39:56,828
Mister, there is something I'm curious about.

564
00:39:57,358 --> 00:39:58,788
I heard...

565
00:39:59,428 --> 00:40:01,758
humans have four lives.

566
00:40:02,258 --> 00:40:04,888
How many lives have I had?

567
00:40:05,988 --> 00:40:07,358
Can't you tell...

568
00:40:07,858 --> 00:40:09,828
a dead person?

569
00:40:10,758 --> 00:40:11,888
This was...

570
00:40:12,628 --> 00:40:14,628
your first.

571
00:40:16,888 --> 00:40:18,458
Thank goodness.

572
00:40:20,258 --> 00:40:21,988
I still have three more.

573
00:40:41,258 --> 00:40:42,828
I'll go get the tea.

574
00:40:43,158 --> 00:40:44,558
You two can talk.

575
00:41:12,888 --> 00:41:13,928
Do you...

576
00:41:15,598 --> 00:41:17,788
remember what I said before?

577
00:41:19,188 --> 00:41:20,728
The person left behind...

578
00:41:22,158 --> 00:41:24,428
has to live to the full.

579
00:41:25,958 --> 00:41:27,958
You'll cry sometimes,

580
00:41:28,688 --> 00:41:30,228
but you'll also laugh a lot...

581
00:41:30,888 --> 00:41:32,598
and live bravely.

582
00:41:34,628 --> 00:41:37,458
That's the proper response to the love you were given.

583
00:41:48,358 --> 00:41:49,928
How can it be like this?

584
00:41:51,428 --> 00:41:53,358
How can you do this?

585
00:41:53,828 --> 00:41:55,228
I'm sorry.

586
00:41:57,598 --> 00:41:59,328
I'm so sorry.

587
00:42:07,528 --> 00:42:10,388
Look at me. Let me...

588
00:42:10,728 --> 00:42:13,158
see your face. Please?

589
00:42:20,598 --> 00:42:21,758
Mister.

590
00:42:22,258 --> 00:42:24,058
You forgot to grant...

591
00:42:24,428 --> 00:42:26,328
one of my three wishes.

592
00:42:29,188 --> 00:42:31,098
Can you grant me that wish now?

593
00:42:32,488 --> 00:42:35,028
Don't be heartbroken for too long.

594
00:42:35,328 --> 00:42:37,488
I'll come see you again.

595
00:42:37,628 --> 00:42:39,528
Wait for me...

596
00:42:39,888 --> 00:42:42,258
and don't make it rain too much.

597
00:42:43,258 --> 00:42:45,358
It'll cause trouble.

598
00:42:46,628 --> 00:42:48,458
That's three wishes, not one.

599
00:42:49,728 --> 00:42:51,388
How am I supposed to live without you?

600
00:42:51,388 --> 00:42:53,388
I'll be gone for just a while.

601
00:42:55,328 --> 00:42:56,958
I promise.

602
00:42:58,158 --> 00:42:59,388
This time,

603
00:43:00,358 --> 00:43:01,728
I'll come to you.

604
00:43:04,558 --> 00:43:05,828
I will...

605
00:43:06,788 --> 00:43:08,688
come looking for you.

606
00:43:09,388 --> 00:43:13,488
In our next life, I will make sure to be born with a long life...

607
00:43:13,688 --> 00:43:16,228
and stay by your side for a long while.

608
00:43:17,628 --> 00:43:19,488
I will beg the divinity...

609
00:43:20,688 --> 00:43:23,258
to let me do just that.

610
00:43:33,828 --> 00:43:35,988
When everyone else leaves...

611
00:43:36,988 --> 00:43:38,428
Please...

612
00:43:38,958 --> 00:43:40,728
take care of this man.

613
00:43:46,588 --> 00:43:48,258
This is the tea of oblivion.

614
00:43:48,958 --> 00:43:50,728
It'll remove...

615
00:43:51,558 --> 00:43:53,228
your memories from your life.

616
00:43:56,458 --> 00:43:57,528
I won't...

617
00:43:58,358 --> 00:43:59,988
drink the tea.

618
00:44:05,988 --> 00:44:07,258
I think...

619
00:44:08,088 --> 00:44:10,228
I have to go now.

620
00:44:16,358 --> 00:44:17,758
I'll be back soon.

621
00:44:19,158 --> 00:44:20,758
I'll go running...

622
00:44:24,328 --> 00:44:26,488
and come back running.

623
00:44:30,958 --> 00:44:32,188
You have to come.

624
00:44:32,458 --> 00:44:35,588
Even if it takes 100 years or 200 years.

625
00:44:35,988 --> 00:44:37,528
I'll wait for you.

626
00:44:38,058 --> 00:44:39,888
So...

627
00:45:22,958 --> 00:45:24,128
See you...

628
00:45:24,788 --> 00:45:26,258
again.

629
00:46:31,028 --> 00:46:34,258
(GOBLIN)

630
00:46:43,258 --> 00:46:45,228
(BRIDE)

631
00:46:46,188 --> 00:46:48,588
In loving memory of...

632
00:46:49,828 --> 00:46:51,358
beloved goblin's bride.

633
00:46:54,058 --> 00:46:55,728
May she rest in peace.

634
00:47:07,188 --> 00:47:08,188
(IN LOVING MEMORY OF BELOVED GOBLIN'S BRIDE.)

635
00:47:08,188 --> 00:47:09,358
(MAY SHE REST IN PEACE.)

636
00:47:20,428 --> 00:47:22,488
(BELOVED, BRIDE, REST IN PEACE)

637
00:47:56,258 --> 00:47:58,088
That day,

638
00:47:58,858 --> 00:48:00,958
Missing Soul walked through...

639
00:48:01,158 --> 00:48:02,828
the tears of someone.

640
00:48:04,558 --> 00:48:08,358
Tides of time got carried away...

641
00:48:09,058 --> 00:48:11,028
by the rainfall.

642
00:48:12,488 --> 00:48:13,858
It was...

643
00:48:14,558 --> 00:48:15,828
a very long rain.

644
00:48:18,388 --> 00:48:19,888
Missing Soul...

645
00:48:20,188 --> 00:48:22,758
left this world without a guardian...

646
00:48:23,388 --> 00:48:26,428
after leaving one behind.

647
00:48:28,428 --> 00:48:32,258
A very lonely and beautiful guardian.

648
00:48:41,558 --> 00:48:42,928
She must have...

649
00:48:43,388 --> 00:48:44,858
met her mom by now.

650
00:48:53,488 --> 00:48:55,028
What is that hairpin?

651
00:48:55,588 --> 00:48:57,588
You didn't pay for that, did you?

652
00:48:57,588 --> 00:48:59,558
No, this is of my dad's taste.

653
00:48:59,558 --> 00:49:02,188
Then wear it when he's around. Why do you have it on now?

654
00:49:02,188 --> 00:49:05,688
I love my dad whether he's around or not.

655
00:49:05,688 --> 00:49:07,658
So mind your own business and shut your mouth.

656
00:49:09,158 --> 00:49:11,688
I don't even have a dad who can buy me one of those.

657
00:49:11,788 --> 00:49:13,128
I don't get it.

658
00:49:13,958 --> 00:49:16,358
Gosh, why do you have to get all serious?

659
00:49:19,328 --> 00:49:21,158
What are you looking at, Lady?

660
00:49:23,888 --> 00:49:25,958
Kids these days are scary.

661
00:49:26,628 --> 00:49:27,828
Whatever.

662
00:49:31,058 --> 00:49:32,158
Sweetheart.

663
00:49:32,328 --> 00:49:35,758
I know you can be like that at your age,

664
00:49:36,058 --> 00:49:39,588
but you don't have to be.

665
00:49:39,588 --> 00:49:41,728
I was only looking at you...

666
00:49:41,728 --> 00:49:44,988
because I couldn't believe how precious you are.

667
00:49:46,628 --> 00:49:48,058
I'm sorry.

668
00:49:48,088 --> 00:49:49,588
I'm sorry.

669
00:49:53,788 --> 00:49:54,958
Do you want more fish cake?

670
00:49:54,958 --> 00:49:56,058
- Yes.
- Yes.

671
00:50:05,358 --> 00:50:08,458
First loves never work out.

672
00:50:09,728 --> 00:50:11,458
You must've loved her a lot.

673
00:50:11,888 --> 00:50:13,158
I guess I did,

674
00:50:13,688 --> 00:50:15,588
considering I can't hold back.

675
00:50:23,058 --> 00:50:24,588
I mean...

676
00:50:24,588 --> 00:50:28,328
I missed you so much that I couldn't breathe.

677
00:50:28,488 --> 00:50:30,128
It was too dangerous.

678
00:50:47,088 --> 00:50:49,058
The woman forgot about you,

679
00:50:49,258 --> 00:50:51,688
but you didn't forget her.

680
00:50:52,988 --> 00:50:54,058
No.

681
00:50:55,058 --> 00:50:57,188
Never for a second or a day.

682
00:51:01,688 --> 00:51:03,328
By the way,

683
00:51:07,128 --> 00:51:10,488
you're not supposed to press my head like that.

684
00:51:16,728 --> 00:51:19,888
You're supposed to pat it like this.

685
00:51:47,328 --> 00:51:51,428
(30 YEARS LATER)

686
00:52:24,588 --> 00:52:27,458
It's your final name card.

687
00:52:28,088 --> 00:52:32,488
Your long punishment has come to an end.

688
00:52:40,658 --> 00:52:42,028
Is it just one?

689
00:52:42,888 --> 00:52:44,128
Yes.

690
00:52:47,758 --> 00:52:51,958
Finally, it's the end of my long punishment.

691
00:52:52,658 --> 00:52:54,258
Congratulations.

692
00:52:54,788 --> 00:52:56,058
Please...

693
00:52:57,788 --> 00:52:59,158
go in peace.

694
00:53:07,188 --> 00:53:08,928
You've helped me a lot.

695
00:53:10,928 --> 00:53:12,388
Thank you.

696
00:53:45,258 --> 00:53:47,458
I won't need to dry clean this anymore.

697
00:54:08,488 --> 00:54:09,858
You said...

698
00:54:11,128 --> 00:54:13,088
I wouldn't hear from you.

699
00:54:20,328 --> 00:54:22,258
Your news came anyway.

700
00:54:48,128 --> 00:54:49,688
It's my last job.

701
00:54:50,458 --> 00:54:51,658
Take care.

702
00:54:52,558 --> 00:54:53,928
You too.

703
00:54:56,258 --> 00:54:58,628
Regardless of the time or the appearance you wear,

704
00:54:59,828 --> 00:55:01,188
be happy.

705
00:55:02,628 --> 00:55:05,488
I've had a good life until now.

706
00:55:07,088 --> 00:55:09,928
- Don't make it rain.
- Don't worry.

707
00:55:11,158 --> 00:55:12,988
This has been my job for a long while.

708
00:55:16,928 --> 00:55:20,358
Once the washing is done, make sure to hang the laundry.

709
00:55:24,328 --> 00:55:27,388
When you're done with that, come to the tea house.

710
00:55:28,588 --> 00:55:30,828
I plan to break the rules just one more time.

711
00:55:31,588 --> 00:55:33,428
I'm leaving anyway.

712
00:56:00,258 --> 00:56:03,088
You haven't aged at all.

713
00:56:03,188 --> 00:56:05,258
You're still just as handsome.

714
00:56:06,428 --> 00:56:07,958
Have you been well?

715
00:56:08,088 --> 00:56:10,528
You said I wouldn't hear from you.

716
00:56:11,228 --> 00:56:12,888
I had forgotten...

717
00:56:13,928 --> 00:56:17,158
that the man I was seeing was a grim reaper.

718
00:56:17,988 --> 00:56:21,728
I forgot that you would find out.

719
00:56:22,628 --> 00:56:24,058
I've missed you.

720
00:56:24,928 --> 00:56:26,828
I knew you would.

721
00:56:45,188 --> 00:56:49,188
I've always wanted to put it on you properly, at least once.

722
00:56:49,828 --> 00:56:53,888
I'm sorry I forced it on you so meanly that time.

723
00:56:54,758 --> 00:56:58,258
I've missed you a lot.

724
00:56:59,788 --> 00:57:01,588
I knew you would.

725
00:57:03,228 --> 00:57:06,928
You are the last deceased soul...

726
00:57:07,458 --> 00:57:09,358
that I am leading.

727
00:57:10,188 --> 00:57:11,628
I see.

728
00:57:12,988 --> 00:57:15,958
Then what's next?

729
00:57:16,358 --> 00:57:18,058
What happens to us?

730
00:57:19,158 --> 00:57:21,458
Is this our happy ending?

731
00:57:22,858 --> 00:57:27,188
This was your third life.

732
00:57:28,558 --> 00:57:30,058
What about you?

733
00:57:30,688 --> 00:57:31,928
I don't know.

734
00:57:33,088 --> 00:57:34,488
I guess...

735
00:57:35,828 --> 00:57:38,888
this may be the last time.

736
00:57:41,788 --> 00:57:44,128
Your brother is here.

737
00:57:45,158 --> 00:57:46,328
Outside.

738
00:57:53,358 --> 00:57:55,528
You still don't care about your brother.

739
00:57:55,528 --> 00:57:59,258
I am happy I get to see you at least like this...

740
00:57:59,888 --> 00:58:01,458
before I go.

741
00:58:01,458 --> 00:58:03,588
It is because I made a good friend.

742
00:58:07,028 --> 00:58:11,258
I'm sorry for going first and leaving you behind.

743
00:58:11,728 --> 00:58:13,788
Please take care of yourself.

744
00:58:14,228 --> 00:58:18,028
Let's meet again someday.

745
00:58:18,588 --> 00:58:19,858
Be happy,

746
00:58:20,388 --> 00:58:22,028
my ugly sister.

747
00:59:20,188 --> 00:59:21,928
My sister,

748
00:59:24,328 --> 00:59:25,958
my friend,

749
00:59:28,958 --> 00:59:30,728
and my bride...

750
00:59:34,258 --> 00:59:35,688
have all left.

751
00:59:39,358 --> 00:59:40,988
And as always,

752
00:59:42,542 --> 00:59:45,172
I am left all alone.

753
01:00:14,371 --> 01:00:15,501
Cheer up.

754
01:00:19,033 --> 01:00:21,163
Do you know why sandwiches come in pairs?

755
01:00:21,163 --> 01:00:23,003
To share with someone else.

756
01:00:23,003 --> 01:00:24,733
Take it.

757
01:00:25,533 --> 01:00:29,333
There are lots of jobs in this world. We'll find one.

758
01:00:29,570 --> 01:00:30,640
Eat up.

759
01:00:34,903 --> 01:00:36,403
You're young.

760
01:00:36,403 --> 01:00:38,163
I know you're frustrated.

761
01:00:39,003 --> 01:00:40,703
Try to cheer up, though.

762
01:00:40,803 --> 01:00:42,733
Some people shine...

763
01:00:44,433 --> 01:00:45,833
later on in life.

764
01:00:49,333 --> 01:00:51,033
Every life is touched...

765
01:00:52,933 --> 01:00:55,563
by a deity at least once.

766
01:00:57,463 --> 01:01:00,033
Just when you're drifting away from the world,

767
01:01:00,963 --> 01:01:04,033
if someone nudged you back in the right direction,

768
01:01:04,933 --> 01:01:06,103
that would be...

769
01:01:06,363 --> 01:01:09,403
when the deity chose to visit you.

770
01:01:10,433 --> 01:01:11,963
I have to go.

771
01:01:14,233 --> 01:01:15,663
Mr. Kim.

772
01:01:17,503 --> 01:01:19,403
Go this way instead.

773
01:01:19,963 --> 01:01:22,763
You will meet someone who needs your help.

774
01:01:24,503 --> 01:01:26,163
Thanks for the sandwich.

775
01:01:35,263 --> 01:01:37,963
Do you know anything about cars?

776
01:01:37,963 --> 01:01:39,163
Yes.

777
01:01:39,833 --> 01:01:42,963
I can tell that this one's not running.

778
01:01:44,163 --> 01:01:45,763
Can I help you?

779
01:01:47,963 --> 01:01:49,363
Do you know about cars?

780
01:01:49,363 --> 01:01:51,903
I've been fixing them for about 20 years.

781
01:01:53,763 --> 01:01:55,033
Let's have a look.

782
01:01:55,033 --> 01:01:57,133
Why didn't you call your insurance company?

783
01:01:57,133 --> 01:01:58,733
They'd sort things out for you.

784
01:02:00,263 --> 01:02:01,833
Did you call the insurance company?

785
01:02:01,833 --> 01:02:05,803
I got distracted when you opened the hood.

786
01:02:05,903 --> 01:02:07,533
I'll call right away.

787
01:02:07,663 --> 01:02:09,033
I believe...

788
01:02:11,203 --> 01:02:14,103
I was meant to meet you.

789
01:02:14,103 --> 01:02:15,263
Were we?

790
01:02:17,103 --> 01:02:19,533
That's a romantic thought, Sir.

791
01:02:19,933 --> 01:02:23,533
Yes. I'm a bit of a romantic.

792
01:02:23,663 --> 01:02:24,903
There we go.

793
01:03:31,933 --> 01:03:34,203
As I sent the lantern flying that night,

794
01:03:35,133 --> 01:03:37,163
I prayed that my sister, in her future...

795
01:03:38,033 --> 01:03:40,263
and my master, in his future...

796
01:03:41,733 --> 01:03:44,033
would meet again one day.

797
01:03:45,833 --> 01:03:48,463
And when they meet again,

798
01:03:49,033 --> 01:03:50,433
that they be happy.

799
01:03:51,733 --> 01:03:53,103
That had been my wish.

800
01:04:00,003 --> 01:04:01,103
What's this?

801
01:04:01,103 --> 01:04:02,403
I arrest people right away,

802
01:04:02,403 --> 01:04:03,733
handcuff them without hesitation...

803
01:04:03,733 --> 01:04:05,363
and read them their rights.

804
01:04:05,363 --> 01:04:07,003
You have the right to remain silent,

805
01:04:07,003 --> 01:04:08,403
the right to refuse to testify...

806
01:04:08,403 --> 01:04:11,303
I asked what this is about. Is that a hard question to ask?

807
01:04:11,303 --> 01:04:14,103
You asked me to show you how I act out an arrest.

808
01:04:14,163 --> 01:04:17,233
I just... I asked you to show me,

809
01:04:17,233 --> 01:04:18,733
not actually handcuff me.

810
01:04:18,733 --> 01:04:20,903
Your criminal's over there.

811
01:04:22,863 --> 01:04:25,433
Oh, is she the criminal?

812
01:04:25,663 --> 01:04:28,533
You looked more like one. Sorry.

813
01:04:31,633 --> 01:04:33,563
Don't I look like a detective?

814
01:04:33,563 --> 01:04:36,233
At 1st glance, 2nd glance and 3rd glance,

815
01:04:36,233 --> 01:04:37,763
you look like a criminal.

816
01:04:37,763 --> 01:04:41,363
How dare you. What makes you think I'm a criminal?

817
01:04:41,463 --> 01:04:44,033
Did I steal your heart or something?

818
01:04:45,033 --> 01:04:47,403
You look like the hostess of a gambling den.

819
01:04:47,403 --> 01:04:49,263
From head to toe.

820
01:04:49,263 --> 01:04:51,233
I just look like one.

821
01:04:51,233 --> 01:04:54,403
I'm working undercover. Undercover.

822
01:04:54,403 --> 01:04:57,703
We're pretending this is 2016.

823
01:04:59,033 --> 01:05:00,403
Forget it.

824
01:05:00,403 --> 01:05:02,933
Director, who is this guy?

825
01:05:02,933 --> 01:05:04,463
Why is he so rude?

826
01:05:04,463 --> 01:05:06,963
Didn't I introduce you two?

827
01:05:06,963 --> 01:05:09,803
He's our consultant, a detective from a violent crimes unit.

828
01:05:09,803 --> 01:05:12,333
I'm Lee Hyuk from Gangnam Police Station.

829
01:05:18,663 --> 01:05:20,303
Lee Hyuk? No way.

830
01:05:21,233 --> 01:05:22,303
I heard that.

831
01:05:26,903 --> 01:05:29,663
Don't get any ideas.

832
01:05:29,663 --> 01:05:31,333
I'm an actress...

833
01:05:31,333 --> 01:05:33,303
and we're filming nearby.

834
01:05:34,133 --> 01:05:36,333
The crew didn't book a hotel...

835
01:05:36,333 --> 01:05:39,663
so I'm here because I don't have a choice.

836
01:05:45,503 --> 01:05:47,203
I'm her stylist.

837
01:05:47,903 --> 01:05:50,033
I have only one free room.

838
01:05:52,333 --> 01:05:54,033
I can't believe...

839
01:05:54,033 --> 01:05:57,133
why there's always only one free room.

840
01:05:57,133 --> 01:06:00,103
That's too bad. We'll take it.

841
01:06:01,963 --> 01:06:03,203
Quickly, please.

842
01:06:03,503 --> 01:06:05,763
We could try looking for another hotel...

843
01:06:05,763 --> 01:06:07,603
but we'd only get sore legs.

844
01:06:07,603 --> 01:06:10,033
Sore legs become swollen.

845
01:06:10,033 --> 01:06:13,403
The more sleep I get the nicer my skin will be tomorrow.

846
01:06:14,233 --> 01:06:16,533
Why didn't they book a room for the actress?

847
01:06:16,533 --> 01:06:18,173
I never wanted to know.

848
01:06:18,363 --> 01:06:19,803
Here's the key.

849
01:06:21,133 --> 01:06:23,603
Lead the way, stylist.

850
01:06:26,763 --> 01:06:28,103
Do you have a room?

851
01:06:28,703 --> 01:06:31,463
Sorry, I only have one left.

852
01:06:33,763 --> 01:06:35,203
Pretend you didn't hear that.

853
01:06:37,803 --> 01:06:39,133
I didn't hear anything.

854
01:06:41,403 --> 01:06:43,963
So what will we do now?

855
01:06:46,633 --> 01:06:48,933
- What do you mean?
- Like...

856
01:06:48,933 --> 01:06:52,033
"Should we date? Meet up regularly?"

857
01:06:52,033 --> 01:06:55,263
"I like you." When will you say things like that?

858
01:06:55,263 --> 01:06:57,003
Aren't you going to?

859
01:06:58,173 --> 01:06:59,633
Should I say that first?

860
01:07:00,033 --> 01:07:02,833
Should I, then? I'm an actress.

861
01:07:02,833 --> 01:07:04,803
I'm already annoyed that I liked you first.

862
01:07:05,503 --> 01:07:07,133
Who said you liked me first?

863
01:07:07,133 --> 01:07:09,803
Everyone does. Are they all wrong?

864
01:07:09,803 --> 01:07:11,033
- Yes.
- How?

865
01:07:11,033 --> 01:07:12,603
I liked you first.

866
01:07:12,903 --> 01:07:14,263
That's my state...

867
01:07:14,433 --> 01:07:17,433
No, that's my confession.

868
01:07:20,463 --> 01:07:21,933
My goodness.

869
01:07:22,103 --> 01:07:23,763
Just a step too late...

870
01:07:23,763 --> 01:07:25,733
and I might have liked you first.

871
01:07:27,173 --> 01:07:28,603
Give me your hand.

872
01:07:44,833 --> 01:07:47,933
- What's this?
- Consider it like a handcuff.

873
01:07:48,173 --> 01:07:50,433
You just stole my heart.

874
01:07:51,763 --> 01:07:53,263
Do you see this?

875
01:07:53,263 --> 01:07:55,703
They call you the Grim Reaper.

876
01:07:55,703 --> 01:07:58,033
Isn't this a bribe?

877
01:08:00,963 --> 01:08:02,863
Arrest me, then.

878
01:08:13,963 --> 01:08:17,233
Is this our first day together?

879
01:08:31,733 --> 01:08:34,173
Are you going somewhere, Sir?

880
01:08:34,803 --> 01:08:36,703
I'd like to go for a walk.

881
01:08:37,303 --> 01:08:39,603
Avoid the main street if you can.

882
01:08:39,763 --> 01:08:43,173
Some Korean students are visiting and they're noisy.

883
01:08:44,033 --> 01:08:46,833
- I shouldn't be long.
- Of course, Sir.

884
01:09:27,803 --> 01:09:28,963
I found him.

885
01:09:29,503 --> 01:09:32,303
There is no sadness that lasts for eternity.

886
01:09:32,673 --> 01:09:34,673
There is no love that lasts for eternity either.

887
01:09:34,833 --> 01:09:36,033
I'm going to vote that there is.

888
01:09:36,033 --> 01:09:39,033
Which one are you voting for? Love or sadness?

889
01:09:39,133 --> 01:09:40,633
Sad love.

890
01:10:14,587 --> 01:10:15,887
Mister.

891
01:10:17,203 --> 01:10:18,833
You know who I am, right?

892
01:10:22,203 --> 01:10:24,033
The first and the last...

